---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL.endsWith('/') ? import.meta.env.BASE_URL : `${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}/`;
---

<BaseLayout title="Adult Path | Soroban Dojo">
  <section class="panel content-prose">
    <p class="eyebrow">Adult path</p>
    <h1>Structured self-study with practical rhythm</h1>
    <p>This path keeps explanations direct, practice disciplined, and progress easy to continue across short study sessions.</p>
    <ul>
      <li>10–20 minute sessions</li>
      <li>Clear objectives and prerequisites</li>
      <li>Review recommendations for weak points</li>
    </ul>
    <div class="hero-actions">
      <a class="button" href={`${base}levels/l0`}>Start at Foundations</a>
      <a class="button button-secondary" href={`${base}curriculum`}>View full curriculum</a>
      <a class="button button-secondary" href={`${base}practice`}>Go to practice</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="split-grid">
    <article class="panel content-prose">
      <p class="eyebrow">First week</p>
      <h2>A practical starter rhythm</h2>
      <ol>
        <li><strong>Day 1:</strong> Learn parts and place value without rushing into arithmetic.</li>
        <li><strong>Day 2:</strong> Read and set two-rod numbers until the layout feels predictable.</li>
        <li><strong>Day 3:</strong> Add and subtract on one rod in one focused practice session.</li>
        <li><strong>Day 4:</strong> Use one worksheet or daily drill pack to test recall under light pressure.</li>
        <li><strong>Day 5:</strong> Review weak points in practice mode instead of pushing to a new topic too early.</li>
      </ol>
      <p class="muted">Consistency matters more than length. Ten honest minutes count.</p>
    </article>

    <article class="panel content-prose">
      <p class="eyebrow">First win</p>
      <h2>A clean confidence check</h2>
      <p>By the end of the first week, this path aims for one clean reading-and-calculation loop: understand place value, read a two-rod number, and complete one short one-rod problem without guessing.</p>
      <div class="hero-actions">
        <a class="button" href={`${base}lessons/l0/parts-of-the-soroban`}>Start the week</a>
        <a class="button button-secondary" href={`${base}lessons/l0/reading-two-rod-numbers`}>Read the first win</a>
        <a class="button button-secondary" href={`${base}exercises/l1/add-four-and-four`}>Solve the first win</a>
      </div>
    </article>
  </section>

  <section class="panel content-prose">
    <p class="eyebrow">Best next steps</p>
    <h2>After the basics feel stable</h2>
    <div class="hero-actions">
      <a class="button" href={`${base}study-plan`}>Open study plan</a>
      <a class="button button-secondary" href={`${base}daily-drills`}>Generate a daily drill pack</a>
      <a class="button button-secondary" href={`${base}practice`}>Open structured practice</a>
      <a class="button button-secondary" href={`${base}paths/children`}>Compare the children path</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
